WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:18.606 --> 00:00:20.524
Our Gangsu Group...

3
00:00:20.524 --> 00:00:23.591
<i>[Episode 7]</i>
cherishes our cleaning employees.

4
00:00:24.176 --> 00:00:25.954
We are considerate of them.

5
00:00:30.811 --> 00:00:33.972
Therefore, CEO Byun Gang Su...

6
00:00:34.557 --> 00:00:38.856
has decided to not use external
contractors for cleaning services.

7
00:00:38.856 --> 00:00:40.429
He will hire them directly.

8
00:00:40.429 --> 00:00:44.576
He decided to make that
announcement on this very day.

9
00:00:44.576 --> 00:00:47.409
What? Is that true?

10
00:00:47.985 --> 00:00:49.417
Hyuk didn't mention that.

11
00:00:49.417 --> 00:00:50.912
I never heard that.

12
00:00:53.182 --> 00:00:54.683
Hyuk.

13
00:00:54.683 --> 00:00:56.380
- What's going on?
- Hey.

14
00:00:56.380 --> 00:00:58.445
What's happening?

15
00:00:59.875 --> 00:01:01.087
Is it true?

16
00:01:01.087 --> 00:01:03.200
Is that true?

17
00:01:03.881 --> 00:01:06.603
Changing temporary
employees to full-time?

18
00:01:06.603 --> 00:01:08.822
All of those employees?

19
00:01:10.834 --> 00:01:13.274
CEO Byun Gang Su.

20
00:01:13.274 --> 00:01:18.560
I truly thank you for this
very meaningful decision.

21
00:01:21.066 --> 00:01:22.989
- It's true?
- Really? Oh my.

22
00:01:22.989 --> 00:01:25.405
CEO Byun Gang Su!
Thank you!

23
00:01:25.405 --> 00:01:27.634
Thank you!

24
00:01:27.634 --> 00:01:29.730
Give him a round of applause!

25
00:01:35.674 --> 00:01:38.243
That little punk.

26
00:01:41.414 --> 00:01:43.490
CEO Byun! CEO!

27
00:01:43.490 --> 00:01:45.406
Is that true?

28
00:01:45.406 --> 00:01:47.983
Please give us a comment.

29
00:01:49.652 --> 00:01:51.007
Just one comment.

30
00:01:51.007 --> 00:01:53.984
Hyuk, you little rascal.

31
00:02:04.058 --> 00:02:05.456
Come here.

32
00:02:05.456 --> 00:02:10.143
Hey, you insane little punk.

33
00:02:11.775 --> 00:02:14.456
When did I ever decide that?

34
00:02:15.086 --> 00:02:18.568
Who said you could say that?

35
00:02:20.205 --> 00:02:22.359
They clean the Gangsu Group building.

36
00:02:22.359 --> 00:02:25.195
It's strange that they're not
employees of Gangsu Group.

37
00:02:25.195 --> 00:02:27.343
So, what?

38
00:02:27.343 --> 00:02:30.127
You dare to protest your
father's company?

39
00:02:30.127 --> 00:02:32.126
I wasn't there as your son.

40
00:02:32.126 --> 00:02:34.139
I was there as the cleaner,
Byun Hyuk.

41
00:02:34.139 --> 00:02:35.937
So...

42
00:02:35.937 --> 00:02:38.588
you're going to become
a fighter for rights overnight?

43
00:02:38.588 --> 00:02:39.902
It's not that.

44
00:02:39.902 --> 00:02:41.247
I know what's going on.

45
00:02:41.247 --> 00:02:43.576
The main contractor abuses
its power over contractors.

46
00:02:43.576 --> 00:02:45.737
Service contractors
abuse power over the employees.

47
00:02:45.737 --> 00:02:49.396
It's never-ending.
That's how it is.

48
00:02:49.396 --> 00:02:51.318
I know it all too.

49
00:02:53.486 --> 00:02:57.950
You don't know what you're talking about.

50
00:03:05.530 --> 00:03:08.068
What were you doing?
What were you doing!

51
00:03:08.068 --> 00:03:11.111
- Father!
- You should've stopped it!

52
00:03:11.111 --> 00:03:12.818
Stop it, Father!

53
00:03:12.818 --> 00:03:15.277
Oh, you'd better let go.
Let go of me!

54
00:03:15.277 --> 00:03:16.657
Don't hit Jae Hoon, please.

55
00:03:16.657 --> 00:03:18.328
- Just hit me.
- Hey!

56
00:03:18.328 --> 00:03:20.548
- Don't hit other people.
- Let go!

57
00:03:20.548 --> 00:03:23.137
I said don't hit others!

58
00:03:43.566 --> 00:03:46.210
How dare you?

59
00:03:56.911 --> 00:03:58.281
Why, you little...

60
00:03:58.281 --> 00:04:03.074
All right, let's both die here today.

61
00:04:03.074 --> 00:04:04.403
You rascal.

62
00:04:04.403 --> 00:04:06.663
Get up now, punk.

63
00:04:06.663 --> 00:04:09.153
I... I have something to say.

64
00:04:09.153 --> 00:04:10.868
Joon.

65
00:04:16.004 --> 00:04:17.500
Who are you?

66
00:04:19.425 --> 00:04:21.995
Hey, Secretary Park.
What were you doing!

67
00:04:21.995 --> 00:04:23.019
Please leave.

68
00:04:23.019 --> 00:04:25.774
Just a moment.
I just need one moment.

69
00:04:28.380 --> 00:04:33.209
Didn't Gangsu Group contract out the
cleaners in order to save labor costs?

70
00:04:33.209 --> 00:04:36.850
But, when the contractors hire cleaners,
you pay a high commission fee.

71
00:04:36.850 --> 00:04:42.954
Meanwhile, the cleaners get poor
benefits, pay, and unfair dismissal.

72
00:04:42.954 --> 00:04:46.266
So? What does that
have to do with me?

73
00:04:46.266 --> 00:04:48.199
What I'm trying say is...

74
00:04:48.199 --> 00:04:53.221
if Gangsu Group hired cleaners directly,
there would be no difference in cost.

75
00:04:53.221 --> 00:04:55.940
Also, the cleaning staff
wouldn't suffer under contractors.

76
00:04:55.940 --> 00:05:00.538
If the costs are the same,
why would I have to do such a thing?

77
00:05:00.538 --> 00:05:03.922
"A person's heart is more
important than money."

78
00:05:03.922 --> 00:05:06.120
"To create employees who care"

79
00:05:06.120 --> 00:05:08.319
"owners must first
understand their hearts."

80
00:05:08.319 --> 00:05:12.718
Third line on page 470 of your
book, "Human Management."

81
00:05:12.718 --> 00:05:15.682
Didn't you write that yourself, CEO Byun?

82
00:05:18.641 --> 00:05:19.911
You read my book?

83
00:05:19.911 --> 00:05:22.552
Between employees
who think of it as their company

84
00:05:22.552 --> 00:05:25.331
and those who consider it temporary...

85
00:05:25.331 --> 00:05:28.283
who do you think would work harder?

86
00:05:34.293 --> 00:05:37.067
Are you a cleaner, as well?

87
00:05:37.067 --> 00:05:40.093
No, I got fired yesterday.

88
00:05:40.093 --> 00:05:43.317
Then I have no reason to listen to you.

89
00:05:43.317 --> 00:05:48.548
You should work here, at the least,
to request something from me.

90
00:05:49.887 --> 00:05:51.617
You're nothing here.

91
00:05:51.617 --> 00:05:56.105
You can talk all you want and show off,
but what's the use?

92
00:05:56.105 --> 00:06:02.115
If you're so great,
you should become an employee here.

93
00:06:02.115 --> 00:06:06.680
Full-time employment is silly.

94
00:06:08.810 --> 00:06:09.846
What?

95
00:06:09.846 --> 00:06:13.567
You work so hard to get it,
but you lose your job in your 40s.

96
00:06:13.567 --> 00:06:19.004
People waste time, money,
and their lives just to get that job.

97
00:06:37.637 --> 00:06:39.384
You're a coward.

98
00:06:40.576 --> 00:06:42.471
A coward?

99
00:06:43.718 --> 00:06:45.593
- Are you talking about me?
- Yes.

100
00:06:45.593 --> 00:06:48.473
You're scared and running
before even starting.

101
00:06:48.473 --> 00:06:53.557
You have lots of excuses,
and you haven't even tried.

102
00:06:54.502 --> 00:06:56.446
Coward.

103
00:07:12.516 --> 00:07:13.999
Joon, I'm so sorry.

104
00:07:13.999 --> 00:07:15.696
I'll apologize on behalf of my father.

105
00:07:15.696 --> 00:07:17.391
Joon.

106
00:07:44.963 --> 00:07:47.348
Was this it?

107
00:07:47.348 --> 00:07:49.915
Your plan to do whatever you could?

108
00:07:50.459 --> 00:07:54.244
At least, I didn't die.

109
00:07:55.108 --> 00:07:59.360
Since things worked out like this,
I'll keep trying.

110
00:07:59.360 --> 00:08:01.031
I mean it.

111
00:08:04.041 --> 00:08:07.728
No, this is more than enough.

112
00:08:10.302 --> 00:08:14.062
Don't get yourself hit over
something that won't work out.

113
00:08:16.007 --> 00:08:17.519
I'll get going.

114
00:08:33.845 --> 00:08:36.214
- This is Strategic Planning.
- This is Strategic Planning.

115
00:08:36.214 --> 00:08:37.322
There will be an announcement.

116
00:08:37.322 --> 00:08:39.501
Please wait for
the official announcement.

117
00:08:39.501 --> 00:08:41.424
Our department doesn't handle that.

118
00:08:41.424 --> 00:08:44.316
Yes, I'm sorry.

119
00:08:46.731 --> 00:08:49.644
I'm sorry I couldn't put a stop to it.

120
00:08:49.644 --> 00:08:52.774
Wasn't it your job before to
keep an eye on that second son?

121
00:08:52.774 --> 00:08:57.332
That guy came and
caused a scene at your event.

122
00:08:57.332 --> 00:08:59.654
Does it make sense
that you didn't know about it?

123
00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:05.104
Hey, do you know how much money
we spent on this project?

124
00:09:05.104 --> 00:09:09.803
Yet, no one is interested
in the new food item.

125
00:09:09.803 --> 00:09:11.714
Everyone is asking about
the cleaners instead.

126
00:09:11.714 --> 00:09:16.142
What are you going to do?
What are you going to about it!

127
00:09:16.142 --> 00:09:17.421
I'm sorry.

128
00:09:17.421 --> 00:09:19.868
Is "sorry" going to cut it?

129
00:09:19.868 --> 00:09:21.047
Oh.

130
00:09:22.198 --> 00:09:23.657
Yes.

131
00:09:24.356 --> 00:09:28.124
We are not responsible for the cleaners.

132
00:09:28.124 --> 00:09:32.037
Nothing's been confirmed, so please
wait for an official announcement.

133
00:09:32.037 --> 00:09:33.413
Yes.

134
00:09:36.038 --> 00:09:37.951
Move!

135
00:09:44.221 --> 00:09:46.028
Are you all crazy?

136
00:09:46.028 --> 00:09:49.163
What were you thinking going up there?

137
00:09:49.163 --> 00:09:52.510
You trusted in the CEO's son
and caused that scene?

138
00:09:52.510 --> 00:09:56.758
I could lose my job
because of you people!

139
00:09:56.758 --> 00:09:59.649
Hey, stop thinking so negatively.

140
00:09:59.649 --> 00:10:01.078
He is the CEO's son.

141
00:10:01.078 --> 00:10:02.158
You never know.

142
00:10:02.158 --> 00:10:04.472
CEO Byun might do everything
that his son asked for.

143
00:10:04.472 --> 00:10:07.703
- That is true.
- He might.

144
00:10:11.770 --> 00:10:13.941
Oh, what's wrong?

145
00:10:13.941 --> 00:10:15.951
Did someone hit you?

146
00:10:16.451 --> 00:10:21.019
Do what his son asked for?
Yeah, right.

147
00:10:21.019 --> 00:10:23.866
It's all over. It's over.

148
00:10:26.652 --> 00:10:28.495
So annoying.

149
00:10:28.495 --> 00:10:30.020
To his own son!

150
00:10:43.693 --> 00:10:49.804
Even if he's angry,
how could he do this to his son?

151
00:10:49.804 --> 00:10:52.806
I guess it was a part of the process.

152
00:10:52.806 --> 00:10:54.596
I tried doing what I could.

153
00:10:54.596 --> 00:10:57.056
I'm sorry things worked out this way.

154
00:10:57.056 --> 00:11:01.121
Why would you be sorry? We're fine.

155
00:11:01.121 --> 00:11:07.773
Telling all those people that
we are important was more than enough.

156
00:11:07.773 --> 00:11:10.942
Yeah, you were cool.

157
00:11:10.942 --> 00:11:12.481
Thank you.

158
00:11:12.481 --> 00:11:14.761
Where did Joon go, anyway?

159
00:11:14.761 --> 00:11:16.923
She followed you to the CEO's office.

160
00:11:16.923 --> 00:11:18.731
Didn't you see her?

161
00:11:22.364 --> 00:11:24.296
Eat this.

162
00:11:25.937 --> 00:11:27.735
- You eat one too, Honey.
- Okay.

163
00:11:27.735 --> 00:11:29.256
Here you go.

164
00:11:29.256 --> 00:11:32.503
Yum. It's sweet.

165
00:11:32.503 --> 00:11:37.193
Oh, it's winter already.

166
00:11:37.193 --> 00:11:38.966
Every day, it's colder.

167
00:11:38.966 --> 00:11:40.309
- Good, right?
- Yes.

168
00:11:40.309 --> 00:11:41.716
Is it good?

169
00:11:43.201 --> 00:11:44.503
Here.

170
00:12:11.700 --> 00:12:14.149
I'm here, Dad.

171
00:12:15.243 --> 00:12:17.783
Sorry it's been so long.

172
00:12:19.683 --> 00:12:21.668
<i>You're a coward.</i>

173
00:12:22.677 --> 00:12:25.828
You're scared and running
before even starting.

174
00:12:31.140 --> 00:12:36.164
You have lots of excuses,
and you haven't even tried.

175
00:12:36.164 --> 00:12:38.241
Coward.

176
00:12:39.433 --> 00:12:41.493
Am I really?

177
00:12:44.922 --> 00:12:50.254
Am I really... a coward?

178
00:13:35.020 --> 00:13:36.740
Jae Hoon.

179
00:13:42.817 --> 00:13:45.269
Joon's not home yet.

180
00:13:46.461 --> 00:13:49.621
Why are you like that?

181
00:13:49.621 --> 00:13:51.971
You only think about yourself, don't you?

182
00:13:51.971 --> 00:13:56.322
You don't care if others get hurt
or have a hard time because of you.

183
00:13:56.322 --> 00:13:58.912
Only your life matters to you.

184
00:13:58.912 --> 00:14:01.182
I'm really sorry, Jae Hoon.

185
00:14:01.182 --> 00:14:05.173
I didn't mean to ruin the event.

186
00:14:05.173 --> 00:14:11.660
It was really important
to the cleaning employees.

187
00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:13.567
Cleaning employees?

188
00:14:13.567 --> 00:14:16.339
Since when did you care
about people like that?

189
00:14:16.339 --> 00:14:17.403
Jae Hoon.

190
00:14:17.403 --> 00:14:19.916
If you're going to cause problems...

191
00:14:19.916 --> 00:14:21.870
do it outside the company.

192
00:14:21.870 --> 00:14:24.765
Don't cause a headache
for so many people.

193
00:14:25.748 --> 00:14:29.870
I'm getting really tired of you.

194
00:14:37.937 --> 00:14:39.714
<i>About Hyuk...</i>

195
00:14:40.416 --> 00:14:42.966
What do you think of him?

196
00:14:42.966 --> 00:14:45.363
I don't know much,
but he sure has a lot of spirit.

197
00:14:45.363 --> 00:14:46.797
Yeah?

198
00:14:47.772 --> 00:14:50.100
You think so too, right?

199
00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:52.020
That kid...

200
00:14:52.020 --> 00:14:55.248
I wondered what he would be able to do.

201
00:14:55.248 --> 00:14:59.938
He has a more ambitious spirit
than I thought.

202
00:15:02.706 --> 00:15:05.869
While we're on the topic...

203
00:15:05.869 --> 00:15:10.453
why don't you take him into your
Strategic Planning team?

204
00:15:10.947 --> 00:15:13.466
See if he can make it or not.

205
00:15:13.466 --> 00:15:17.539
Take him in and put him to work.

206
00:15:19.451 --> 00:15:22.764
I can't do that, CEO Byun.

207
00:15:22.764 --> 00:15:24.464
You can't?

208
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:27.032
Why not?

209
00:15:27.032 --> 00:15:31.317
If you want him on my team,
do it officially.

210
00:15:31.317 --> 00:15:36.078
As it turns out,
we're hiring new interns.

211
00:15:36.078 --> 00:15:41.128
Getting hired fairly
by his own merits into Gangsu

212
00:15:41.128 --> 00:15:44.408
is what's best for you and Hyuk.

213
00:15:44.408 --> 00:15:46.423
Oh, no.

214
00:15:46.423 --> 00:15:49.782
He couldn't even graduate
college in the US.

215
00:15:49.782 --> 00:15:53.551
He's only a high school graduate
and has no experience.

216
00:15:53.551 --> 00:15:58.365
How can he get hired by our company?

217
00:15:59.091 --> 00:16:02.902
We won't be looking at academics,
gender, or age this time.

218
00:16:02.902 --> 00:16:05.865
We won't be looking at the
resume they've built up.

219
00:16:05.865 --> 00:16:10.871
We'll be choosing based on
their capabilities and character.

220
00:16:10.871 --> 00:16:12.864
So...

221
00:16:12.864 --> 00:16:15.833
you're saying Hyuk can get in?

222
00:16:15.833 --> 00:16:18.971
You're curious to know
if he can make it or not.

223
00:16:18.971 --> 00:16:23.293
If he can make it,
he should get in.

224
00:16:45.264 --> 00:16:49.217
<i>The intern applications start today.
Don't be stubborn.</i>

225
00:17:01.441 --> 00:17:04.152
Is it true that you won't be
looking at the resume?

226
00:17:04.152 --> 00:17:08.292
- Yes.
- Oh, Gangsu Group's doing good work.

227
00:17:08.292 --> 00:17:10.301
Go on.

228
00:17:12.137 --> 00:17:14.914
What? You want me to what?

229
00:17:14.914 --> 00:17:18.654
Apply for the open call for interns.

230
00:17:19.201 --> 00:17:23.661
If you pass everything
and become an intern

231
00:17:23.661 --> 00:17:27.162
I'll think about hiring
the cleaning staff directly.

232
00:17:27.162 --> 00:17:31.356
Apply today if you want to be
held responsible for your words.

233
00:17:31.356 --> 00:17:34.801
Father, this isn't right.

234
00:17:35.390 --> 00:17:37.973
- Why not?
- An intern?

235
00:17:39.964 --> 00:17:44.137
How could I get in?
You know my education and resume.

236
00:17:44.137 --> 00:17:45.691
This isn't a proper negotiation.

237
00:17:45.691 --> 00:17:48.781
You're basically saying you won't do it.

238
00:17:48.781 --> 00:17:51.432
A person who makes claims
without even knowing a thing.

239
00:17:51.432 --> 00:17:53.942
Is that a proper negotiation?

240
00:17:53.942 --> 00:17:56.343
- Father.
- I'm done talking.

241
00:17:56.343 --> 00:18:00.568
It's up to you if you
want to accept it or not.

242
00:18:17.117 --> 00:18:18.653
Hello?

243
00:18:20.914 --> 00:18:23.419
Wh... what? Intern?

244
00:18:24.852 --> 00:18:27.193
Who? You?

245
00:18:27.193 --> 00:18:29.055
Yes, me.

246
00:18:29.055 --> 00:18:30.786
Does this make sense?

247
00:18:30.786 --> 00:18:32.893
He wants me to apply to be an intern.

248
00:18:32.893 --> 00:18:37.334
He says I need to pass so he'll
consider hiring the cleaners.

249
00:18:37.334 --> 00:18:39.273
What do you think this means?

250
00:18:39.273 --> 00:18:43.019
What else? He's saying screw off.

251
00:18:43.942 --> 00:18:47.349
Well, there's no need
to say it so directly.

252
00:18:47.349 --> 00:18:48.721
Your education is lacking.

253
00:18:48.721 --> 00:18:53.076
All you have going for you
is that you're the CEO's son.

254
00:18:53.076 --> 00:18:55.535
It's not like the CEO
is giving you the position.

255
00:18:55.535 --> 00:18:58.579
He wants you to fight fairly
with others and pass on your own.

256
00:18:58.579 --> 00:19:00.259
Yes.

257
00:19:00.259 --> 00:19:02.574
He must be telling me to screw off.

258
00:19:02.574 --> 00:19:04.689
I heard they're not looking at
the resume this time.

259
00:19:04.689 --> 00:19:07.307
Even so, there's a limit to it.

260
00:19:07.307 --> 00:19:10.938
At the final stages, what would
they look at if not the resume?

261
00:19:10.938 --> 00:19:12.127
Hold on.

262
00:19:12.127 --> 00:19:18.723
So, this whole thing about "no resumes"
was all about the company's image?

263
00:19:18.723 --> 00:19:21.026
Yet, you were pushing me to apply?

264
00:19:21.026 --> 00:19:22.683
Even though you knew it was all a lie.

265
00:19:22.683 --> 00:19:25.035
Joon, you're going to
apply to be an intern too?

266
00:19:25.035 --> 00:19:27.035
Don't be ridiculous.

267
00:19:27.035 --> 00:19:30.403
You and Hyuk are on a different level.

268
00:19:30.403 --> 00:19:34.394
Yes, Joon is on a different level
of intelligence than me.

269
00:19:34.394 --> 00:19:35.644
I'm glad that you know.

270
00:19:35.644 --> 00:19:37.664
There's no need for you
to be conflicted.

271
00:19:37.664 --> 00:19:39.844
You will fail that intern interview.

272
00:19:39.844 --> 00:19:42.384
Gangsu Group will re-sign
with the cleaning contractors.

273
00:19:42.384 --> 00:19:47.517
Then CEO Min will continue
to reap the benefits.

274
00:19:47.517 --> 00:19:50.384
Well, then there's
nothing to think about.

275
00:19:50.384 --> 00:19:51.925
Just apply.

276
00:19:51.925 --> 00:19:53.959
Yes, right?

277
00:19:53.959 --> 00:19:55.294
What?

278
00:19:55.294 --> 00:19:56.753
- Do what?
- Hey, Baek Joon.

279
00:19:56.753 --> 00:19:58.929
You said you'd get them hired.

280
00:19:58.929 --> 00:20:01.196
Their lives are in your hands right now.

281
00:20:01.196 --> 00:20:02.867
You're quitting without even trying?

282
00:20:02.867 --> 00:20:04.730
No, that's not it.

283
00:20:04.730 --> 00:20:06.959
Don't egg him on to do things
he can't be responsible for.

284
00:20:06.959 --> 00:20:11.398
Then you shouldn't have done that
performance at the event at all, Hyuk.

285
00:20:11.398 --> 00:20:12.874
That is true.

286
00:20:12.874 --> 00:20:15.943
No. Don't even think about it.
You can't do it.

287
00:20:15.943 --> 00:20:17.469
Yes, I can't.

288
00:20:17.469 --> 00:20:20.155
A man is giving up before trying?

289
00:20:20.155 --> 00:20:22.540
Yes, that's not right.

290
00:20:22.540 --> 00:20:24.538
I told you not to do it.

291
00:20:24.538 --> 00:20:27.142
I told you to do it.

292
00:20:38.567 --> 00:20:42.567
Your father told Hyuk
to apply for an internship?

293
00:20:42.567 --> 00:20:44.064
I know, right?

294
00:20:44.064 --> 00:20:47.263
Even if he is angry,
why would he tell Hyuk to intern?

295
00:20:47.263 --> 00:20:48.957
It's a bit too much.

296
00:20:49.634 --> 00:20:51.971
What in the world is he thinking?

297
00:20:54.069 --> 00:20:56.772
Is there anything you know, Mother?

298
00:20:56.772 --> 00:20:58.334
<i>You told me to give him wings.</i>

299
00:20:58.334 --> 00:21:00.680
<i>What do you mean by that?</i>

300
00:21:00.680 --> 00:21:03.824
If he has wings, he'll fly.

301
00:21:03.824 --> 00:21:06.003
I don't know if he's a phoenix.

302
00:21:06.003 --> 00:21:11.479
I need to throw him to know
if he's an eagle or a baby chick.

303
00:21:13.413 --> 00:21:15.343
Father said that?

304
00:21:15.343 --> 00:21:20.186
I wondered what that meant, at the time.

305
00:21:21.144 --> 00:21:22.493
Hey, Woo Sung.

306
00:21:22.493 --> 00:21:27.131
Do you think your father is trying
to help train Hyuk right now?

307
00:21:27.772 --> 00:21:31.888
Shouldn't you help Hyuk
as his older brother, then?

308
00:21:31.888 --> 00:21:33.776
Come on, Mother.

309
00:21:33.776 --> 00:21:36.224
You know he's just a troublemaker.

310
00:21:36.224 --> 00:21:38.044
How could I help?

311
00:21:38.044 --> 00:21:41.897
Hey, Hyuk didn't turn
his back on you back then.

312
00:21:41.897 --> 00:21:45.176
That young thing was
protecting his older brother...

313
00:21:48.765 --> 00:21:52.240
Never mind. Let's not talk about it.

314
00:21:59.037 --> 00:22:01.486
Oh, I can't do it. I can't.

315
00:22:01.486 --> 00:22:05.203
How can I do it?
Even if they're not looking at resumes.

316
00:22:05.203 --> 00:22:07.555
I need to know something
to pass the tests.

317
00:22:07.555 --> 00:22:10.105
Oh, I can't do it. I can't do it.

318
00:22:26.042 --> 00:22:29.862
Is Hyuk that poorly educated?

319
00:22:29.862 --> 00:22:32.662
I don't really know.

320
00:22:32.662 --> 00:22:35.608
How much of a bad student was he?

321
00:22:35.608 --> 00:22:37.421
It can't be just that.

322
00:22:37.421 --> 00:22:40.429
Yeah, it can't just be about that.

323
00:22:40.429 --> 00:22:42.654
What would happen if he doesn't pass?

324
00:22:42.654 --> 00:22:46.222
That determines whether
we become direct hires or not.

325
00:22:46.222 --> 00:22:49.894
It must be such
an emotional burden, right?

326
00:22:49.894 --> 00:22:51.692
Yeah, yeah.

327
00:23:18.635 --> 00:23:20.634
What brings you by?

328
00:23:20.634 --> 00:23:24.413
I was just curious about where you lived.

329
00:23:24.994 --> 00:23:27.715
It's not as bad as I thought it'd be.

330
00:23:27.715 --> 00:23:29.355
My home is very shabby.

331
00:23:29.355 --> 00:23:31.275
Would you like to go to a cafe nearby?

332
00:23:31.275 --> 00:23:32.964
It's okay, Jae Hoon.

333
00:23:32.964 --> 00:23:35.105
Don't worry about that.

334
00:23:35.105 --> 00:23:38.365
There's a cafe five minutes away.

335
00:23:38.365 --> 00:23:41.217
He says he was curious
about where I lived.

336
00:23:42.012 --> 00:23:44.286
Then I should show him.

337
00:23:47.484 --> 00:23:49.230
Come on, Brother.

338
00:23:56.393 --> 00:23:58.586
Wait here.

339
00:24:34.411 --> 00:24:36.086
Are you okay with coffee, Woo Sung?

340
00:24:36.086 --> 00:24:39.861
No, I don't drink coffee after 6:00 p.m.

341
00:24:40.506 --> 00:24:42.844
Then I'll drink alone.

342
00:24:45.656 --> 00:24:48.835
Ah, okay. I'm recharged.

343
00:24:48.835 --> 00:24:51.259
It’s a bit small, right?

344
00:24:51.259 --> 00:24:54.369
Sit wherever you feel comfortable.

345
00:24:59.635 --> 00:25:02.527
So, Father told you
to apply for the internship.

346
00:25:02.527 --> 00:25:03.844
That's what I heard.

347
00:25:03.844 --> 00:25:05.396
Yes.

348
00:25:13.384 --> 00:25:14.842
What is it?

349
00:25:15.935 --> 00:25:18.432
You said you needed money.

350
00:25:18.432 --> 00:25:20.965
I gave you more than enough in there.

351
00:25:20.965 --> 00:25:23.207
Take it and leave Korea for a while.

352
00:25:23.207 --> 00:25:27.548
Go on vacation
and give your mind a break.

353
00:25:27.548 --> 00:25:33.102
Also, don't take Father's offer
too seriously.

354
00:25:34.436 --> 00:25:36.595
Don't act up, kid.

355
00:25:37.978 --> 00:25:40.968
You wouldn't even
pass the intern interview.

356
00:25:40.968 --> 00:25:44.406
What are you rambling on about
direct hiring of cleaners?

357
00:25:45.137 --> 00:25:49.696
Just shut your mouth and live quietly.

358
00:25:51.517 --> 00:25:53.545
That's what he means by it.

359
00:26:02.332 --> 00:26:03.893
Hyuk.

360
00:26:06.154 --> 00:26:08.166
You've done enough.

361
00:26:08.166 --> 00:26:11.273
You've shown your presence enough.

362
00:26:12.829 --> 00:26:17.351
Stop now and go have fun
somewhere outside of this country.

363
00:26:17.351 --> 00:26:21.721
I'll give you whatever you need
while you're there, okay?

364
00:26:27.079 --> 00:26:28.960
<i>Please, Hyuk.</i>

365
00:26:29.651 --> 00:26:33.154
I'll do whatever you need.

366
00:26:33.730 --> 00:26:35.771
Save me just this once.

367
00:26:35.771 --> 00:26:39.277
You know I'll die if our father knows.

368
00:26:39.277 --> 00:26:41.963
You're the only person who can help me.

369
00:26:41.963 --> 00:26:44.500
You're the only one...

370
00:26:46.369 --> 00:26:49.978
I'll do anything you want, okay?

371
00:26:52.471 --> 00:26:56.594
So, Hyuk. Save me this once.

372
00:26:57.228 --> 00:26:59.074
I'm begging like this.

373
00:27:03.607 --> 00:27:07.042
My goodness. I can't believe this.

374
00:27:07.042 --> 00:27:08.912
You little bastard.

375
00:27:08.912 --> 00:27:10.596
Honey!

376
00:27:10.596 --> 00:27:12.955
Have you no fear?

377
00:27:12.955 --> 00:27:17.308
You took the car out tonight
and hit a person?

378
00:27:18.502 --> 00:27:20.690
What? What happened?

379
00:27:23.146 --> 00:27:25.501
Hyuk... Hyuk.

380
00:27:26.922 --> 00:27:28.270
I'm sorry.

381
00:27:28.270 --> 00:27:30.076
Turn yourself in!

382
00:27:30.441 --> 00:27:34.257
Take responsibility
for the things you've done!

383
00:27:35.441 --> 00:27:39.310
Honey, please. Our Hyuk is still young.

384
00:27:39.310 --> 00:27:43.340
He still has his future.
Please help him this once.

385
00:27:43.340 --> 00:27:45.557
I don't know.

386
00:27:47.096 --> 00:27:49.143
Honey!

387
00:27:49.143 --> 00:27:52.342
Honey, Honey!

388
00:27:52.342 --> 00:27:54.126
Honey!

389
00:28:11.101 --> 00:28:12.969
This is amusing.

390
00:28:15.076 --> 00:28:17.838
When you say you'll do anything for me...

391
00:28:20.388 --> 00:28:22.931
it means you're desperate.

392
00:28:23.676 --> 00:28:25.113
Right?

393
00:28:30.097 --> 00:28:32.779
Now that I think about it...

394
00:28:34.382 --> 00:28:36.977
there was only one thing
you could do for me.

395
00:28:36.977 --> 00:28:40.597
Ah, I'm not upset by it though.

396
00:28:43.592 --> 00:28:46.002
For one thing, it's not fun anymore.

397
00:28:47.342 --> 00:28:52.189
Whatever it is...
people doing things for me.

398
00:28:55.037 --> 00:28:59.755
You're not saying you're really going
to apply for this internship, are you?

399
00:29:04.082 --> 00:29:07.340
Honestly, I wasn't up for the task.

400
00:29:07.340 --> 00:29:11.303
But you showed up here
worrying about me.

401
00:29:11.303 --> 00:29:15.805
I feel pathetic at the fact
that I was scared.

402
00:29:16.413 --> 00:29:18.405
So, you're doing it?

403
00:29:18.952 --> 00:29:21.625
You'll cheer me on, right, Brother?

404
00:29:51.788 --> 00:29:56.000
Tell him he doesn't need
to feel too burdened by us.

405
00:29:56.000 --> 00:29:57.598
Everyone has to make his own living.

406
00:29:57.598 --> 00:30:00.020
People have to live their own lives.

407
00:30:00.020 --> 00:30:03.816
Of course, he doesn't need
to feel responsible for us at all.

408
00:30:03.816 --> 00:30:05.243
That's right.

409
00:30:17.836 --> 00:30:19.888
Are you just leaving like that?

410
00:30:20.840 --> 00:30:23.049
What is he thinking?

411
00:30:23.049 --> 00:30:24.585
Do you know anything?

412
00:30:24.585 --> 00:30:27.311
Thinking? Nothing, really.

413
00:30:27.311 --> 00:30:30.519
I just got mad on my own
and got upset.

414
00:30:31.569 --> 00:30:33.979
Is that really it?

415
00:30:33.979 --> 00:30:35.336
Hm?

416
00:30:35.336 --> 00:30:36.832
I'm sure that's all it is.

417
00:30:36.832 --> 00:30:41.539
He probably only said it out of
embarrassment in front of his brother.

418
00:30:42.284 --> 00:30:45.451
- Don't worry. I'll take care of it.
- No.

419
00:30:45.451 --> 00:30:47.376
Don't do a single thing.

420
00:30:48.063 --> 00:30:51.192
Let him go for the internship.

421
00:30:51.192 --> 00:30:56.021
He needs to see how low and
how much of a nobody he is.

422
00:30:56.021 --> 00:30:57.946
He needs to get out there to see.

423
00:31:13.461 --> 00:31:15.760
Joon, what did you just say?

424
00:31:15.760 --> 00:31:18.046
Let's do it together, that intern test.

425
00:31:18.046 --> 00:31:20.386
Really? You too?

426
00:31:22.070 --> 00:31:23.497
Why, suddenly?

427
00:31:23.497 --> 00:31:26.714
I can't leave you
to get screwed by yourself.

428
00:31:26.714 --> 00:31:27.778
Joon.

429
00:31:27.778 --> 00:31:30.171
Of course, it's not free,
so don't expect too much.

430
00:31:30.171 --> 00:31:32.378
Intern tests all have three rounds.

431
00:31:32.378 --> 00:31:34.821
First round, human resources
screening test.

432
00:31:34.821 --> 00:31:36.579
Second round, a practical skills test.

433
00:31:36.579 --> 00:31:38.141
Third round, a personal interview.

434
00:31:38.141 --> 00:31:40.670
For every round you pass,
200,000 won and you get special training.

435
00:31:40.670 --> 00:31:44.039
If you pass the whole thing,
I get a bonus of 100,000 on top.

436
00:31:44.039 --> 00:31:46.556
How about it?

437
00:31:46.556 --> 00:31:49.250
That doesn't matter to me.

438
00:31:50.095 --> 00:31:52.806
Special training though? What's that?

439
00:31:52.806 --> 00:31:55.387
They won't accept just anyone,
even if they don't look at resumes.

440
00:31:55.387 --> 00:31:58.855
That means they need
other means to evaluate you.

441
00:31:58.855 --> 00:32:00.304
Language.

442
00:32:01.289 --> 00:32:02.890
Math.

443
00:32:02.890 --> 00:32:04.037
Deduction.

444
00:32:04.613 --> 00:32:07.964
Spatial perception, current events.

445
00:32:08.828 --> 00:32:11.143
You need master all of these things.

446
00:32:11.143 --> 00:32:12.397
All of this?

447
00:32:12.397 --> 00:32:14.105
Yes.

448
00:32:14.105 --> 00:32:18.715
Last of all... this one too.

449
00:32:21.263 --> 00:32:22.885
<i>[Human Management]</i>

450
00:32:31.647 --> 00:32:35.269
<i>[Interning is my path to survival!]</i>

451
00:32:41.814 --> 00:32:43.696
You think that will work?

452
00:32:49.799 --> 00:32:52.163
You agree, right?

453
00:33:00.083 --> 00:33:01.515
<i>Hey, Byun Hyuk.</i>

454
00:33:02.067 --> 00:33:03.906
You're not studying, are you?

455
00:33:03.906 --> 00:33:05.623
Get back to studying now!

456
00:33:05.623 --> 00:33:08.311
Oh, oh. Okay, I will.

457
00:33:08.311 --> 00:33:11.230
I'll study. I will.

458
00:33:11.230 --> 00:33:13.498
Joon knows me so well.

459
00:33:51.390 --> 00:33:52.992
Eat while you study.

460
00:33:55.595 --> 00:33:57.451
Yum, this rice.

461
00:33:57.451 --> 00:33:59.535
It's so good.

462
00:34:00.173 --> 00:34:02.837
The ramen noodles are really great.

463
00:34:17.538 --> 00:34:21.378
These are the questions they've used
in the past three years.

464
00:34:21.378 --> 00:34:23.755
It's a study guide of past exams.

465
00:34:23.755 --> 00:34:26.398
It was very hard to get this.

466
00:34:26.398 --> 00:34:27.565
Use this to study.

467
00:34:27.565 --> 00:34:29.394
We'll make good use of it, Madam Ahn.

468
00:34:29.394 --> 00:34:30.797
Here.

469
00:34:30.797 --> 00:34:34.447
It's a study guide that Madam Ahn
worked hard to get, so memorize it.

470
00:34:35.306 --> 00:34:38.740
There's so much I have to memorize, Joon.

471
00:34:43.068 --> 00:34:45.550
Ah... yum.

472
00:34:46.771 --> 00:34:48.958
- Keep it up.
- Okay.

473
00:35:21.385 --> 00:35:26.262
I managed to get
these documents from the company.

474
00:35:32.527 --> 00:35:33.793
Thank you, Mister.

475
00:35:33.793 --> 00:35:35.659
No need to thank me.

476
00:35:38.588 --> 00:35:40.876
Oh, you're resting.

477
00:36:05.900 --> 00:36:12.364
<font color="#80ffff">[DF Ver] E07 Revolutionary Love</font>
<font color="#ff00ff">-= Ruo Xi =-</font>

478
00:36:36.078 --> 00:36:37.796
Is it going well?

479
00:36:39.652 --> 00:36:41.277
I don't know.

480
00:36:42.031 --> 00:36:45.982
I'm just doing what Joon tells me to.

481
00:36:45.982 --> 00:36:48.585
It's so hard, my friend.

482
00:36:52.129 --> 00:36:56.616
I've been pooping blood.

483
00:36:59.955 --> 00:37:01.919
<i>Why are you pushing so hard?</i>

484
00:37:01.919 --> 00:37:04.897
No matter how much you rile him up,
Hyuk won't make it.

485
00:37:04.897 --> 00:37:06.071
He won't pass.

486
00:37:06.071 --> 00:37:09.980
Even if he passes rounds one and two,
he won't make it past round three.

487
00:37:09.980 --> 00:37:11.491
Why?

488
00:37:14.955 --> 00:37:17.080
Chief Byun Woo Sung will fail him.

489
00:37:17.080 --> 00:37:21.710
Why does he go that far
to keep Hyuk in check?

490
00:37:22.433 --> 00:37:25.643
He's not keeping him in check.
He looks down on him.

491
00:37:25.643 --> 00:37:27.692
A younger brother is giving it a try.

492
00:37:27.692 --> 00:37:29.873
The older brother
purposely gets in the way.

493
00:37:29.873 --> 00:37:31.654
Is that merely looking down on him?

494
00:37:31.654 --> 00:37:33.035
I think differently.

495
00:37:33.035 --> 00:37:36.558
Are you getting involved in
Hyuk's sibling fights too?

496
00:37:36.558 --> 00:37:40.393
You could even end up being in charge
of taking care of Hyuk instead of me.

497
00:37:40.393 --> 00:37:42.473
What? Can't I do that?

498
00:37:42.473 --> 00:37:45.584
You do it, so why can't I do it?

499
00:37:45.584 --> 00:37:48.274
Are you serious about that nonsense?

500
00:37:48.274 --> 00:37:51.035
You said you've been friends
with Hyuk since kindergarten.

501
00:37:51.035 --> 00:37:53.435
Don't you know Hyuk at all?

502
00:37:53.435 --> 00:37:56.299
Then what about you?
What do you know about him?

503
00:37:56.299 --> 00:37:57.939
You haven't known him that long.

504
00:37:57.939 --> 00:38:02.140
At least, I know the burden of
responsibility he's carrying.

505
00:38:02.140 --> 00:38:06.511
Do you think Hyuk knows what
the word "responsibility" means?

506
00:38:06.511 --> 00:38:08.580
If he didn't know,
why would he be doing this?

507
00:38:08.580 --> 00:38:10.062
He could live life in comfort.

508
00:38:10.062 --> 00:38:12.844
Do you really not know?
It's all because of you.

509
00:38:12.844 --> 00:38:16.265
Because you keep telling him to do it
and encouraging him.

510
00:38:16.265 --> 00:38:21.089
He doesn't even know what he's doing
and he's running in head first.

511
00:38:23.375 --> 00:38:27.069
What if it is because of me?
Is that wrong?

512
00:38:29.806 --> 00:38:33.094
What do you mean by that?

513
00:38:33.094 --> 00:38:36.727
Whatever the reason,
he's doing something with sincerity.

514
00:38:36.727 --> 00:38:38.727
Isn't that good enough?

515
00:38:40.694 --> 00:38:42.757
<i>What is it?</i>

516
00:38:42.757 --> 00:38:45.116
That burden of responsibility?

517
00:38:52.306 --> 00:38:54.995
